23:27.457 --> 23:29.299
out there now? The big problem that's out there now 
is that the scholarly monograph is under serious

23:29.439 --> 23:38.066
directs. That is, libraries, the principal 
purchasers of scholarly monographs, are cutting

23:38.126 --> 23:49.737
back and spending more money on technology than 
they are on books. And so every university in

23:49.757 --> 23:55.742
France that publishes scholarly monographs has 
seen their their sales declined dramatically.

24:00.043 --> 24:03.887
That's one of the wisdoms that Frank had. Frank 
knew 20 years ago that scholarly publishing was

24:03.907 --> 24:10.213
deficit publishing. He knew that if he just did 
scholarly monographs, he'd go out of business, or

24:10.313 --> 24:19.583
that the administration would stop supporting 
him. So he said, I'm going to do books that are

24:19.603 --> 24:24.488
regional significance. Those books sell. And I 
like doing them anyway, and I'll keep the rules,

24:26.300 --> 24:35.915
the financial rules away from the door, and I'll 
accomplish what I believe in, and that's the way to

24:26.300 --> 24:35.915
do it. The problem is, you know, that works 
financially, but it doesn't keep the academic

24:36.937 --> 24:43.868
books up. You know, so guys like Ham Hill and Silver 
